00:19:40.390 --> 00:19:41.800
There's the k, here.

00:19:41.800 --> 00:19:55.460
S is equal to minus k, log
sum over i, pi, log pi.

00:19:55.460 --> 00:19:59.820
Another great result.

00:19:59.820 --> 00:20:02.110
Now if you system is isolated.

00:20:02.110 --> 00:20:03.840
If you have an isolated
system, that means

00:20:03.840 --> 00:20:05.610
that the energy --

00:20:05.610 --> 00:20:07.170
You've got your boundary.

00:20:07.170 --> 00:20:10.080
The boundary doesn't let
energy go in and out.

00:20:10.080 --> 00:20:13.350
Doesn't let the number of
particles go in and out.

00:20:13.350 --> 00:20:17.120
Every single microstate is going
to have the same energy.

00:20:17.120 --> 00:20:19.010
If this system is isolated.

00:20:19.010 --> 00:20:22.000
The only thing you're going
to change is the

00:20:22.000 --> 00:20:23.720
positions of the particles.

00:20:23.720 --> 00:20:25.390
Or their vibrational energy.

00:20:25.390 --> 00:20:25.940
Or something.

00:20:25.940 --> 00:20:28.550
But let's just stick
with translation.

00:20:28.550 --> 00:20:30.690
You're just going to change
the positions.

00:20:30.690 --> 00:20:34.950
You're not going to
change the energy.

00:20:34.950 --> 00:20:42.530
So, if the system is isolated,
then the degeneracy of your

00:20:42.530 --> 00:20:45.260
energy is just a number of ways
that you can flip the

00:20:45.260 --> 00:20:46.840
positions around.

00:20:46.840 --> 00:20:49.960
Indistinguishable ways.

00:20:49.960 --> 00:20:54.580
So the probability is just one
over the number of possible

00:20:54.580 --> 00:21:00.060
ways of switching positions
around for your particles.

00:21:00.060 --> 00:21:30.650
So for an isolated system,
all microstates

00:21:30.650 --> 00:21:35.830
have the same energy.

00:21:35.830 --> 00:21:39.580
We can set that equal to zero
as our reference point.

00:21:39.580 --> 00:21:44.090
And the probability of being in
any one microstate is just

00:21:44.090 --> 00:21:45.600
one over the number
of possible ways

00:21:45.600 --> 00:21:48.050
of rearranging things.

00:21:48.050 --> 00:21:53.420
So the probability of been in
any one microstate is one over

00:21:53.420 --> 00:21:56.220
the number of my microstates.

00:21:56.220 --> 00:22:01.030
They all have the same energy.

00:22:01.030 --> 00:22:07.470
Where this is the degeneracy.

00:22:07.470 --> 00:22:14.760
So now when you plug that
